TITLE      Study of (14.0 MeV/u) uranium ions interaction with
            vanadium target
AUTHOR     (G.Sher, M.Ikram Shahzad)
INSTITUTE  (3PAKNIL)
REFERENCE  (J,IMP/E,22,1350045,2013)
           #doi:10.1142/S0218301313500456
FACILITY   (LINAC,2GERGSI) UNILAC accelerator facility.
INC-SOURCE (ATOMI)
INC-SPECT  The incident projectile ions fluence was
            0.9 X10**5 ions/cm2
SAMPLE     2pi target-detector assembly was prepared by vacuum
            deposition of a thin layer (0.56 mg/cm2) of vanadium
            on mica track detector.
DETECTOR   (TRD) The mica (muscovite) detector have chemical
            formula KAl3Si3O10(OH)2, density of ~2.9 g/cm3 and
            refractive index : 1.57.
HISTORY    (20131106C) VS
           (20260417A) VT. Revision in 002. REFERENCE: DOI
            corrected.
